<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1410839" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Rape-2-1.jpg?resize=600%2C350&#038;ssl=1" alt="Grandfather arrested in Delta for defiling seven years old girl" width="600" height="350" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Rape-2-1.jpg?w=760&amp;ssl=1 760w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Rape-2-1.jpg?resize=300%2C175&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Rape-2-1.jpg?resize=58%2C34&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Rape-2-1.jpg?resize=260%2C152&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Rape-2-1.jpg?resize=200%2C117&amp;ssl=1 200w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> OGWASHI-UKU Police Division has arrested a grandfather for allegedly defiling a seven-year-old girl in Ubulu-Uku town, Aniocha South Local Government Area, Delta State. The suspect who was simply identified as Madumeye was accused of inserting his fingers into the vaginal of the young girl, thereby causing her injuries. Our Correspondent reports that the man who was said to be in his early seventies was still in police custody as at press time. A reliable community source told newsmen in Asaba that the mother of the victim who became curious when she noticed unusual behaviour of her daughter, decided to interrogate her. The source who pleaded anonymity, said upon interrogation, the victim told the mother that the suspect used his fingers on her private part, adding that the little girl was taken to the General Hospital, Ubulu-Uku where she was treated with bruises around her vaginal, after which she was discharged. When contacted on the matter, the Public Relations Officer, PPRO in the State, DSP Onome Onovwakpoyeya said she was out of the state and could not confirm the incident. However, a Police source at Ogwashi-Uku, confirmed the incident, adding that the suspect was arrested following complaints lodged by the mother of the victim. The Police source who also pleaded anonymity said the matter was being investigated. Vanguard News Nigeria Asaba-A 45-year-old woman, who runs a private maternity home in Abia State, has been arrested along with three other women over their alleged involvement in the stealing of an eight-month-old baby boy from his parents at Ogwashi-Uku, Delta State. May 9, 2012 In "News" THREE children of the same parents have been arrested at Ubulu-Uku, Delta State for allegedly hacking a widow to death with a saw blade for allegedly having an amorous relationship with their father. January 19, 2011 In "Headlines" ...Court jails man, 31, in Edo for raping seven years old girl By Egufe Yafugborhi & Ozioruva Aliu 30-year-old, Musa Abubakar has admitted defiling his nine-year-old stepdaughter because his wife refused to sleep with him as she always complained of being weak. The suspect reportedly confessed at the State Criminalâ€¦ July 23, 2020 In "Metro"